shortDescription: Hit man John Wick takes his fight against the High Table global as the price on his head grows.

title: Shazam! Fury of the Gods
longDescription: Bestowed with the powers of the gods, Billy Batson and his fellow foster kids are still learning how to juggle teenage life with their adult superhero alter egos. When a vengeful trio of ancient gods arrives on Earth in search of the magic stolen from them long ago, Shazam and his allies get thrust into a battle for their superpowers, their lives, and the fate of the world.
shortDescription: Shazam and his allies must save the world from a vengeful trio of ancient gods.

title: Creed III
longDescription: Still dominating the boxing world, Adonis Creed is thriving in his career and family life. When Damian, a childhood friend and former boxing prodigy resurfaces after serving time in prison, he's eager to prove that he deserves his shot in the ring. The face-off between former friends is more than just a fight. To settle the score, Adonis must put his future on the line to battle Damian -- a fighter who has nothing to lose.
shortDescription: Boxer Adonis Creed puts his future on the line to take on a former friend who has nothing to lose.

title: A Good Person
longDescription: Allison is a young woman with a wonderful fiance, a blossoming career, and supportive family and friends. However, her world crumbles in the blink of an eye when she survives an unimaginable tragedy, emerging from recovery with an opioid addiction and unresolved grief. In the following years, she forms an unlikely friendship with her would-be father-in-law that gives her a fighting chance to put her life back together and move forward.
shortDescription: An opioid addict develops an unlikely friendship with her would-be father-in-law.

title: Inside
longDescription: A high-end art thief becomes trapped inside a luxury, high-tech penthouse in New York's Times Square after his heist doesn't go as planned. Locked inside with nothing but priceless works of art, he must use all his cunning and invention to survive.
shortDescription: A high-end art thief becomes trapped in a luxury, high-tech penthouse in New York's Times Square.

title: Scream VI
longDescription: Four survivors of the Ghostface murders leave Woodsboro behind for a fresh start in New York City. However, they soon find themselves in a fight for their lives when a new killer embarks on a bloody rampage.
shortDescription: A new killer follows four survivors of the Ghostface murders to New York City.

title: Cocaine Bear
longDescription: An oddball group of cops, criminals, tourists and teens converges in a Georgia forest after a 500-pound black bear ingests a large amount of cocaine and goes on a drug-fueled rampage.
shortDescription: A 500-pound black bear ingests a large amount of cocaine and goes on a drug-fueled rampage.

title: Smoking Causes Coughing
longDescription: A group of vigilantes called the "tobacco forces" is falling apart; to rebuild team spirit, their leader suggests that they meet for a week-long retreat before returning to save the world.
shortDescription: A vigilante group called the "tobacco forces" is falling apart, so their leader suggests a retreat.

title: Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania
longDescription: Ant-Man and the Wasp find themselves exploring the Quantum Realm, interacting with strange new creatures and embarking on an adventure that pushes them beyond the limits of what they thought was possible.
shortDescription: Ant-Man and the Wasp embark on a mind-bending adventure in the Quantum Realm.

title: Jacir
longDescription: A young Syrian refugee faces hard truths chasing the American dream on the streets of Memphis, Tenn., while living in poverty, dealing with social injustice and witnessing his neighbor's opioid addiction.
shortDescription: A Syrian refugee faces hard truths chasing the American dream on the streets of Memphis, Tenn.

title: Moving On
longDescription: Two estranged women reunite to seek revenge against the husband of their recently deceased best friend. Along the way, they learn to make peace with the past and each other.
shortDescription: Two estranged women reunite to seek revenge against the husband of their deceased best friend.

title: Everything Everywhere All at Once
longDescription: When an interdimensional rupture unravels reality, an unlikely hero must channel her newfound powers to fight bizarre and bewildering dangers from the multiverse as the fate of the world hangs in the balance.
shortDescription: An unlikely hero uses newfound powers to fight fearsome and bewildering dangers from the multiverse.

title: Full River Red
longDescription: In 12th-century China, an ambassador is killed and a letter meant for the emperor is stolen. As the search for the letter unfolds, alliances are formed, secrets are revealed, and no one can stop the truth that's destined to leave its mark on history.
shortDescription: Secrets are revealed as the search for the emperor's stolen letter unfolds in 12th-century China.

title: One Fine Morning
longDescription: A young single mother raising an 8-year-old daughter struggles to take care of her father, who's been diagnosed with a neurodegenerative disease. While trying to secure a decent nursing home, she runs into a married friend and they begin an affair.
shortDescription: A single mother struggles to take care of her father, who has a neurodegenerative disease.

title: Rodeo
longDescription: A young woman with a passion for riding embeds herself in the underground world of dirt biking.
shortDescription: A young woman with a passion for riding embeds herself in the underground world of dirt biking.

title: Puss in Boots: The Last Wish
longDescription: After burning though eight lives, Puss in Boots sets out on an epic journey to find the mythical Last Wish and restore all nine.
shortDescription: Puss in Boots sets out on an epic journey to find the mythical Last Wish and restore his nine lives.

title: Champions
longDescription: A former minor-league basketball coach receives a court order to manage a team of players with intellectual disabilities. Despite his doubts, he soon realizes that together they can go further than they ever imagined.
shortDescription: A former minor-league basketball coach manages a team of players with intellectual disabilities.

longDescription: After a catastrophic crash on an unknown planet, pilot Mills quickly discovers he's actually stranded on Earth -- 65 million years ago. Now, with only one chance at a rescue, Mills and the only other survivor, Koa, must make their way across an unknown terrain riddled with dangerous prehistoric creatures.
shortDescription: Two survivors of a deadly crash battle prehistoric creatures on Earth -- 65 million years ago.

title: Jesus Revolution
longDescription: In the 1970s, Greg Laurie and a sea of young people descend on sunny Southern California to redefine truth through all means of liberation. Inadvertently, Laurie meets a charismatic street preacher and a pastor who open the doors to a church to a stream of wandering youth. What unfolds is a counterculture movement that becomes the greatest spiritual awakening in American history.
shortDescription: A street preacher and a pastor spark the greatest spiritual awakening in American history.

title: School of Magical Animals
longDescription: Ida attends a new school after her family moves. Her strange teacher announces that all pupils will receive a magical companion, and Ida gets a talking fox named Rabbat. When the animals are in danger, Ida teams up with other kids to save them.
shortDescription: Ida attends a new school and receives a magical companion in the form of a talking fox named Rabbat.

title: In viaggio: The Travels of Pope Francis
longDescription: During the first nine years of his pontificate, Pope Francis visits 53 countries, focusing on the issues of poverty, migration, the environment, solidarity and war.
shortDescription: Pope Francis focuses on the issues of poverty, migration, the environment, solidarity and war.
